The paper discusses software architecture and its mapping to implementation, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). It also introduces a notion of behavioral contract, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal methods (cs.AR). The paper focuses on the domain of Sense/Compute/Control applications, which involves systems and control theory (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
